- 'most listened-to' refers to the number of times the playlist has been played ('play' engagement type); 
- 'top tracks by popularity' refers to the highest 'track_popularity' score;
- 'how well the tracks energize the crowd' refers to the 'danceability' of the tracks, which is a score indicating the track's potential to get people moving.

; For the context of this query, popularity is based on the total number of plays across all playlists; 
; The 'play' engagement type refers to when a user plays a track in a playlist; 
; The average audio features (danceability, energy, and valence) are calculated to provide insights into the characteristics of the top tracks.
